result.formatted_address: E01-E06, Queensway Plaza, 93 Queensway, Admiralty, Hong Kong
result.name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao

reviews.text: They can’t speak English. The meat tastes very sweet and oily noodle so I disliked it. They’re not friendly. Unless you know how to speak Chinese, I feel like Hong Kong restaurants are not easy to tryout. Because most of them don’t know how to speak English.
Great food! Joeie’s service is the best and beyond my expectations.
All the menu ordered tasted fantastic. The place is nice and clean. Service is above Hong Kong average

75 mins of waiting. At which point we were so hungry it may have highten our taste buds. Food is 100% better than the one in Melbourne. Food was cooked very well. Worth 75mins waiting, maybe not. But if you don't have to wait it is worth a try.

Went mid week for dinner. Xlb was good, but not life changing for a Michelin star restaurant. We also had a dessert that was like a azuki bean filled beignet, but was a little soggy and overly sugary. 

Could have been when I went, but this place wouldn’t be my first choice of restaurant for the price/wait.
